---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about PortfolioAtlas — how we calculate FIRE lifestyle costs and why we built this resource."
>
  <div class="container-narrow py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-950 mb-6">
        About PortfolioAtlas
      </h1>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-6">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          PortfolioAtlas answers one simple question: <strong>"If I retire with $X, what kind of
          life can I actually live?"</strong> We break it down city by city, dollar by dollar.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-brand-950 mt-12 mb-4">How We Calculate</h2>
        <p>
          Every city page shows lifestyle breakdowns at five portfolio tiers: <strong>$1M, $2M, $3M,
          $5M, and $10M</strong>. We use the widely-accepted <strong>4% safe withdrawal rate</strong>
          (the "Trinity Study" rule) to calculate your monthly budget:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-brand-50 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 border border-brand-100">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-5 gap-4 text-center">
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">$1M</div>
              <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">$3,333/mo</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">$2M</div>
              <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">$6,667/mo</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">$3M</div>
              <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">$10,000/mo</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">$5M</div>
              <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">$16,667/mo</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">$10M</div>
              <div class="font-bold text-brand-700">$33,333/mo</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>
          For each tier, we research and estimate realistic monthly costs for housing, groceries,
          dining out, healthcare, transportation, entertainment, utilities, and — at higher
          tiers — domestic help and luxury extras.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-brand-950 mt-12 mb-4">The FIRE Score</h2>
        <p>
          Each city receives a <strong>FIRE Score from 1 to 10</strong> based on a combination of
          factors: overall cost of living, healthcare quality and accessibility, safety, ease of
          obtaining residency, English friendliness, internet infrastructure, and how far your
          money goes relative to lifestyle quality.
        </p>
        <p>
          A higher score means your portfolio stretches further while maintaining a high quality
          of life. Cities in Southeast Asia and Latin America tend to score highest, while
          North American and Western European cities score lower due to higher costs — but may
          offer other advantages like proximity to family or familiar culture.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-brand-950 mt-12 mb-4">Important Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          The cost data on PortfolioAtlas is researched and estimated for informational purposes
          only. Actual costs vary based on personal lifestyle choices, exchange rate fluctuations,
          inflation, and individual circumstances.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site does not provide financial, tax, or legal advice. Always consult with qualified
          professionals — a financial advisor, tax specialist, and immigration attorney — before
          making any relocation or retirement decisions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cost data reflects approximate values as of early 2026 and will be periodically reviewed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
